    "A lightweight approach to find such data is to perform principal component analysis (PCA) on the embeddings (Gewers et al., 2021).",
    "Specifically, for each user u, given a set of user history H u = {h i u } where each h i u represents an individual user history sample with index i, we have",
    "Then, we have that W u are the top k principal components of",
    "u, e 2 u,.",
    ", e N u ] ⊤ and the projection of each embedding is z i u = e i u W u."
